Durban - Six alleged drug dealers were arrested for drugs with an estimated street value of R100 000 in Chatsworth, south of Durban. Captain Nqobile Gwala, police spokesperson said members of the Provincial Drug Unit were following up on information regarding the packaging drugs in a flat at Silver Heights Drive, Westcliff, Chatsworth. “Upon arrival at the scene, there were occupants inside the house and capsules were found on the floor. The premises was searched and clear packets of heroin were found in the bedroom. A search was also conducted in the kitchen, packets of capsules with heroin powder and a measuring scale were found hidden under the sink. A total of five suspects were placed under arrest. Whilst the members were busy conducting their investigation another suspect was arrested outside the premises after he was found in possession of heroin,” explained Gwala. “This arrest sends a clear message to drug dealers and drug manufacturers that police in the province are determined to rooting-out the proliferation of drugs in our community. These operations are continuing in KZN province as part of the Safer Festive Season Operations,” said Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner. Gwala said all those who were arrested were aged between 16 and 52 and will appear in the Chatsworth Magistrate’s Court on Monday on charges of dealing drugs and manufacturing of drugs. Daily News